10 Section 1. R.S. 22:1042.1 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
11 §1042.1. Coverage for medically necessary treatment for persons with an
12 acquired brain injury
13 A. Every health coverage plan delivered or issued for delivery in this
14 state shall provide, to the extent permitted by federal law, coverage for
15 medically necessary treatment related to or as a result of an acquired brain
16 injury.
17 B.(1) The coverage provided pursuant to this Section shall not include
18 any lifetime limitation or unreasonable annual limitation of the number of days
19 or sessions of treatment services.
20 (2) Any limitations on rehabilitation services in an inpatient
21 rehabilitation facility shall be separate from and shall not be included in any
22 limitations of post-acute rehabilitation.
23 (3) Any limitations shall be separately stated by the health coverage plan
24 issuer.
25 C. The coverage provided pursuant to this Section shall not be subject
26 to any greater deductible, coinsurance, copayments, or out-of-pocket limits than
27 any other similar benefit provided by the health coverage plan.
