1 D. A health coverage plan shall not deny coverage for medically
2 necessary treatment based solely on the location or setting in which the
3 treatment is provided, if the treatment is provided in a setting that is clinically
4 appropriate for the level of care necessary and in compliance with applicable
5 state licensure, certification, registration, or accreditation requirements.
6 Clinically appropriate settings may include but are not limited to inpatient
7 hospital or rehabilitation facility settings, outpatient and day treatment settings,
8 post-acute residential treatment settings, and home- and community-based
9 settings.
10 E. For any medically necessary treatment covered pursuant to this
11 Section, any adverse determination issued in connection with a preauthorization
12 or utilization review shall be made by a clinical peer reviewer.
13 F. The commissioner shall promulgate rules and regulations, in
14 accordance with the Administrative Procedure Act, to establish a process for an
15 expedited appeal of any adverse determination by a health coverage plan issuer
16 for medically necessary treatment covered pursuant to this Section.
17 G. Medically necessary treatment covered pursuant to this Section shall
18 be provided by individual practitioners and treatment facilities qualified to
19 provide acute care and post-acute care rehabilitation services to a person with
20 an acquired brain injury through possession of the appropriate licenses,
21 accreditation, training, and experience deemed customary and routine in the
22 trade practice.
23 H. For the purposes of this Section, the following definitions apply:
24 (1) "Acquired brain injury" or "ABI" means any injury to the brain
25 which is not a progressive neurologic disorder, hereditary, congenital, or
26 degenerative in nature, and which occurs after birth and may be caused by
27 infectious diseases, metabolic disorders, endocrine disorders, diminished
28 oxygen, brain tumors, toxins, a disease that affects the blood supply to the brain,
29 stroke, or a traumatic brain injury.
30 (2) "Adverse determination" means a determination by a clinical peer
