2 admission, extension of stay, or any other covered ABI service is not medically
3 necessary.
4 (3) "Clinical peer reviewer" means a healthcare professional who has
5 experience in the delivery of treatments and services for persons with acquired
6 brain injuries and possesses a current and valid license, certificate, or
7 registration to provide these treatments and services or, where no provision for
8 a license, certificate or registration exists, is credentialed by the national
9 accrediting body appropriate to the profession.
10 (4) "Cognitive communication therapy" means treatment for problems
11 with communication which have an underlying cause in one or more cognitive
12 deficits rather than a primary language or speech deficit.
13 (5) "Cognitive rehabilitation therapy" means a process of relearning
14 cognitive skills essential for daily living through the coordinated specialized,
15 integrated therapeutic treatments which are provided in dynamic settings
16 designed for efficient and effective relearning following damage to brain cells
17 or brain chemistry due to brain injury.
18 (6) "Community reintegration services" means incremental, guided,
19 real-world therapeutic training to develop skills essential for an individual to
20 participate in life including functional daily activities; to safely live
21 independently; and to participate in the community while avoiding
22 rehospitalization and long-term support needs.
23 (7) "Functional rehabilitation therapy" means a structured approach
24 which emphasizes learning by doing, and focuses relearning a specific task in
25 a prescribed format, with maximum opportunity for repeated correct practice.
26 Functional rehabilitation therapy includes compensatory strategies developed
27 for those skills which are persistently impaired with individuals trained on daily
28 implementation. To ensure acquisition and use, the focus of functional
29 rehabilitation therapy is set on relearning those skills essential for safe daily
30 living in home- and community-based settings.
