1 (8) "Health coverage plan" means any hospital, health, or medical
2 expense insurance policy, hospital or medical service contract, employee welfare
3 benefit plan, contract, or other agreement with a health maintenance
4 organization or a preferred provider organization, health and accident
5 insurance policy, or any other insurance contract of this type in this state,
6 including a group insurance plan or a self-insurance plan. "Health coverage
7 plan" does not include a plan providing coverage for excepted benefits as
8 defined in R.S. 22:1061, limited benefit health insurance plans, short-term
9 policies that have a term of less than twelve months, Medicare, Medicaid, and
10 the Office of Group Benefits programs.
11 (9) "Medically necessary treatment" means healthcare services that are
12 consistent with generally accepted principles of professional medical practice.
13 Medically necessary treatment includes but is not limited to cognitive
14 rehabilitation therapy; cognitive communication therapy; neurocognitive
15 therapy and rehabilitation; neurobehavioral; neurophysiological; and
16 neuropsychological testing; neurofeedback therapy; functional rehabilitation
17 therapy; community reintegration services; post-acute residential treatment
18 services; inpatient services; outpatient and day treatment services; and home-
19 and community-based treatment.
20 (10) "Neurobehavioral therapy" means a set of medical and therapeutic
21 assessments and treatments focused on behavioral impairments associated with
22 brain disease or injury and the amelioration of these impairments through the
23 development of prosocial behavior.
24 (11) "Neurocognitive therapy" means treatment of disorders in which
25 the primary clinical deficit is in cognitive function which has not been present
26 since birth and is a decline from a previously attained level of function.
27 (12) "Neuropsychological testing" means a set of medical and
28 therapeutic assessments and treatments focused on amelioration of cognitive,
29 emotional, psychosocial, and behavioral deficits caused by brain injury.
30 (13) "Post-acute residential treatment" means integrated medical and
